%% Vibook — Sequence diagram: consumer login and JWT-protected API access
%% Render: https://mermaid.live or VS Code Mermaid preview

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Consumer
    participant Mobile as Mobile App
    participant Auth as AuthController
    participant AuthSvc as AuthService
    participant JWT as JwtService
    participant RT as RefreshTokenService
    participant Filter as JwtAuthenticationFilter
    participant API as Protected Controller
    participant DB as MySQL (users, refresh_tokens)

    Note over Consumer,DB: Login — issue access JWT + opaque refresh token

    Consumer->>Mobile: Enter email and password
    Mobile->>Auth: POST /api/v1/auth/login
    Auth->>AuthSvc: login(credentials)
    AuthSvc->>DB: authenticate user (BCrypt)
    AuthSvc->>RT: createRefreshToken(user)
    RT->>DB: save refresh_tokens row
    AuthSvc->>JWT: generateToken(user)
    JWT-->>AuthSvc: HS256 access JWT (24h)
    AuthSvc-->>Auth: AuthResponse
    Auth-->>Mobile: accessToken + refreshToken + user profile
    Mobile->>Mobile: persist tokens (AsyncStorage)

    Note over Consumer,DB: Protected request — Bearer JWT on every call

    Consumer->>Mobile: Open bookings tab
    Mobile->>Filter: GET /api/v1/bookings/me<br/>Authorization: Bearer accessToken
    Filter->>JWT: validate token + extract email
    JWT-->>Filter: valid claims
    Filter->>Filter: set SecurityContext (roles)
    Filter->>API: forward request
    API->>DB: query bookings
    DB-->>API: rows
    API-->>Mobile: 200 BookingResponse[]
    Mobile-->>Consumer: show booking list

    Note over Consumer,DB: Access token expired — refresh without re-login

    Mobile->>Filter: GET /api/v1/bookings/me (expired JWT)
    Filter-->>Mobile: 401 Unauthorized
    Mobile->>Auth: POST /api/v1/auth/refresh { refreshToken }
    Auth->>AuthSvc: refreshAccessToken()
    AuthSvc->>RT: verifyRefreshToken()
    RT->>DB: load + validate refresh_tokens
    AuthSvc->>JWT: generateToken(user)
    Auth-->>Mobile: new accessToken
    Mobile->>Mobile: update stored access token
    Mobile->>Filter: retry GET /api/v1/bookings/me
    Filter->>API: forward (valid JWT)
    API-->>Mobile: 200 BookingResponse[]
